Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force on 1 November
In parallel with its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the Congress's vote on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to the public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of both coming into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by Members and Senators to negotiate and consent to the best rules in order to ensure investor protection and to regulate the activity of entities in detail to ensure that markets operate efficiently.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (NCMV) and encouraging cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new legislation will provide financial advisory services both to specialized firms and to natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial service signatures (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
It also expands the number of systems for the execution of operations on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment service companies to disseminate information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms on the market and requires them to keep a record of all operations they carry out in order to facilitate monitoring by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congress's Economic Commission, a number of amendments were incorporated, among which points out that debt securities are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated by the US debt of high-risk mortgages (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates can perform in Economics and Business 30 years after the Royal Decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was adopted in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work for others, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its services for the marketing of products and the collection of customers to different investment firms at the same time.
